50|$|In North America {{the period}} is {{referred}} to prosaically as the slow news season, or with the phrase dog days of summer. In Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa, the <b>silly</b> <b>season</b> has come {{to refer to the}} Christmas/New Year festive period (which occurs during the summer season in the Southern Hemisphere) on account of the higher than usual number of social engagements where the consumption of alcohol is typical.|$|E
